&s;upport, was &s;eating her&s;elf, uncon&s;ciou&s;ly,
in the iron chair it&s;elf; but &s;uddenly per|ceiving
where &s;he was, &s;he &s;tarted from it
in horror, and &s;prung towards a remote
end of the room. Here again &s;he looked
round for a &s;eat to &s;u&s;tain her, and per|ceived
only a dark curtain, which, de|&s;cending
from the cieling to the floor, was
