Ill as &s;he was, the appearance of this cur|tain
&s;truck her, and &s;he pau&s;ed to gaze
upon it, in wonder and apprehen&s;ion.</P>
<P>It &s;eemed to conceal a rece&s;s of the
chamber; &s;he wi&s;hed, yet dreaded, to
