di&s;tinctly know what good purpo&s;e this
could an&s;wer, and &s;ometimes &s;he even re|coiled
in horror from the expectation of
<PB N="38" REF="40">
his pre&s;ence. She wi&s;hed, al&s;o, to peti|tion,
though &s;he &s;carcely dared to believe
the reque&s;t would be granted, that he
would permit her, &s;ince her aunt was no
