<P>After &s;ome deliberation, &s;he determined
that Montoni &s;hould not be informed of
this event till the morning, for &s;he con&s;i|dered,
that he might,; perhaps, utter &s;ome
inhuman expre&s;&s;ions,, &s;uch as in the pre|&s;ent
temper of her &s;pirits &s;he could not
bear. With Annette alone, therefore,
whom &s;he encouraged by her own exam|ple,
<PB N="95" REF="97">
&s;he performed &s;ome of the la&s;t &s;olemn
offices for the dead, and compelled her&s;elf
to watch during the night, by the body of
her decea&s;ed aunt. During this &s;olemn
