of provi&s;ion on the&s;e wild mountains, &s;oon
compelled the a&s;&s;ailants to rai&s;e the &s;iege.</P>
<P>When Udolpho was once more left to
the quiet po&s;&s;e&s;&s;ion of Montoni, he di&s;|patched
Ugo into Tu&s;cany for Emily,
whom he had &s;ent from con&s;iderations of
her per&s;onal &s;afety, to a place of greater
&s;ecurity, than a ca&s;tle, which was, at that
