<P>&startq;Aye, there is the old clock, &endq; &s;aid Ber|trand,
&startq;there he is &s;till; the cannon
have not &s;ilenced him!&endq;</P>
<P>&startq;No,&endq; an&s;wered Ugo, &startq;he crowed as
loud as the be&s;t of them in the mid&s;t of it
all. There he was roaring out in the
hotte&s;t fire 1 have &s;een this many a day!
I &s;aid that &s;ome of them would have a
hit at the old fellow, but he e&s;caped, and
the tower too.&endq;</P>
<P>The road winding round the ba&s;e of a
<PB N="228" REF="230">
mountain, they now came within view of
