to li&s;ten, but the loud &s;well of the
gu&s;t overcame every other &s;ound. When
the wind &s;unk again, &s;he heard di&s;tinctly,
in the deep pau&s;e that &s;ucceeded, the
&s;weet &s;trings of a lute; but again the ri&s;ing
