&s;wept by; but the &s;ounds were &s;o di&s;tant,
and pa&s;&s;ed &s;o &s;uddenly, that &s;he could
&s;carcely hear them, much le&s;s di&s;tingui&s;h
the words they uttered, or recogni&s;e the
