&s;tored with gay and beautiful ima|gery.</P>
<P>It was on the evening of the &s;eventh day,
that the travellers came within view of
Chateau-le-Blanc, the romantic beauty of
who&s;e &s;ituation &s;trongly impre&s;&s;ed the ima|gination
of Blanche, who ob&s;erved, with
&s;ublime a&s;toni&s;hment, the Pyrenean moun|tains,
which, had been &s;een only at a di&s;|tance
during the day, now ri&s;ing within
a few leagues, with their wild cliffs and
immen&s;e precipices, which the evening
clouds, floating round them, now di&s;|clo&s;ed,
and again veiled. The &s;etting
rays, that tinged their &s;nowy &s;ummits
with a ro&s;eate hue, touched their lower
<PB N="345" REF="347">
points with various colouring, while the
