&s;pot was inhabited by my ance&s;tors.&endq;</P>
<P>The carriage now &s;topped at the cha|teau,
where, at the door of the great hall,
appeared the old &s;teward and the Pari&s;ian
&s;ervants, who had been &s;ent to prepare the
