except the Counte&s;s, who&s;e vacant
mind, overcome by the languor of idle|ne&s;s,
would neither &s;uffer her to be happy
her&s;elf, or to contribute to the happine&s;s
of others. Mademoi&s;elle Bearm, attempt|ing
<PB N="379" REF="381">
to be witty, directed her <HI>badinage</HI>
again&s;t Henri, who an&s;wered, becau&s;e
he could not well avoid it, rather than
from any inclination to notice her, who&s;e
liveline&s;s &s;ometimes amu&s;ed, but who&s;e
conceit and in&s;en&s;ibility often di&s;gu&s;ted
