about the Marchione&s;s. I &s;hould like to
look into the gla&s;s you &s;poke of ju&s;t now,
and &s;ee a few of the circum&s;tances, which
you &s;ay often pa&s;s over it.&endq;</P>
<P>&startq;No, my lady,&endq; replied Doroth&eacute;e;
&startq;if you knew as much as I do, you would
<PB N="410" REF="412">
not, for you would find there a di&s;mal
